00:47:12.647 --> 00:47:14.217
in your head,
because it's very,

00:47:14.217 --> 00:47:17.850
very important.
When you take a complex number,

00:47:17.850 --> 00:47:21.639
it's got a length and it's got
a direction.

00:47:21.639 --> 00:47:24.039
Then, you multiply by a second
complex number,

00:47:24.039 --> 00:47:26.599
you're able to do two things at
the same time.

00:47:26.599 --> 00:47:29.860
You're able to rescale it,
and you're able to rotate it.

00:47:29.860 --> 00:47:32.523
You rescale by the length of
the second factor,

00:47:32.523 --> 00:47:35.940
and you rotate by the angle
carried by the second factor.

00:47:40.269 --> 00:47:43.640
The fact that two operations
are done in one shot is the

00:47:43.640 --> 00:47:47.194
reason complex numbers play an
incredibly important role in

00:47:47.194 --> 00:47:49.293
physics,
and certainly in engineering

00:47:49.293 --> 00:47:50.560
and mathematical physics.

